    <div class="text-container">
      <div style="height: 30vh;"></div>

      <div class="step-block" data-target-scene="1">
        <span class="step-number">01</span>
        <h2>You bring one poem</h2>
        <p>Every month, 12 poets each share one poem. Any form, any voice, any subject. That's it.</p>
        <span class="step-detail">One poem per person. No themes, no prompts. Just whatever you've been writing.</span>
      </div>

      <div class="step-block" data-target-scene="2">
        <span class="step-number">02</span>
        <h2>Four juries are formed</h2>
        <p>The 12 poets are randomly placed into four groups of three. That's your reading group for the month.</p>
        <span class="step-detail">Three poets per room.</span>
      </div>

      <div style="height: 70vh;"></div>

      <div class="step-block" data-target-scene="3">
        <span class="step-number">03</span>
        <h2>Poets become readers</h2>
        <p>The poems move. Each jury receives three poems from a different group, distributed anonymously.</p>
        <p>Jury A reads B's poems. B reads C's. C reads D's. D reads A's.</p>
        <span class="step-detail">Each poem gets read by 3 people. Each person reads 3 poems.</span>
      </div>

      <div style="height: 70vh;"></div>

      <div class="step-block" data-target-scene="4">
        <span class="step-number">04</span>
        <h2>Now you read</h2>
        <p>Read all three poems and help rank your favorites. Leave feedback you'd actually want to get back. The top poems go on the website and Instagram for people to read.</p>
        <span class="step-detail">If you don't review, your poem sits out.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

